<statement>
<p>Suppose <m>\displaystyle{f{{\left({x}\right)}}}=\sqrt{{{x}}}</m> . Give the function for each of the following transformations.</p>
<p>The graph of <m>\displaystyle{f{{\left({x}\right)}}}</m> reflected across the y-axis.</p>
<p><ol style="list-style-type:upper-alpha"><li><m>\displaystyle{f{{\left({x}\right)}}}=\sqrt{{-{x}}}</m></li> 
<li><m>\displaystyle{f{{\left({x}\right)}}}=-\sqrt{{-{x}}}</m></li> 
<li><m>\displaystyle{f{{\left({x}\right)}}}=-\sqrt{{{x}}}</m></li> 
</ol></p>
<p>The graph of <m>\displaystyle{f{{\left({x}\right)}}}</m>  shifted right 2 units</p>
<p><ol style="list-style-type:upper-alpha"><li><m>\displaystyle{f{{\left({x}\right)}}}=\sqrt{{{x}+{2}}}</m></li> 
<li><m>\displaystyle{f{{\left({x}\right)}}}=\sqrt{{{x}}}+{2}</m></li> 
<li><m>\displaystyle{f{{\left({x}\right)}}}=\sqrt{{{x}-{2}}}</m></li> 
<li><m>\displaystyle{f{{\left({x}\right)}}}=\sqrt{{{x}}}-{2}</m></li> 
</ol></p>
<p>The graph of <m>\displaystyle{f{{\left({x}\right)}}}</m>  shifted down 3 units</p>
<p><ol style="list-style-type:upper-alpha"><li><m>\displaystyle{f{{\left({x}\right)}}}=\sqrt{{{x}-{3}}}</m></li> 
<li><m>\displaystyle{f{{\left({x}\right)}}}=\sqrt{{{x}}}-{3}</m></li> 
<li><m>\displaystyle{f{{\left({x}\right)}}}=\sqrt{{{x}+{3}}}</m></li> 
<li><m>\displaystyle{f{{\left({x}\right)}}}=\sqrt{{{x}}}+{3}</m></li> 
</ol></p>
<p>The graph of <m>\displaystyle{f{{\left({x}\right)}}}</m>  shifted right 2 units and shifted up 1 units.</p>
<p><ol style="list-style-type:upper-alpha"><li><m>\displaystyle{f{{\left({x}\right)}}}=\sqrt{{{x}-{2}}}+{1}</m></li> 
<li><m>\displaystyle{f{{\left({x}\right)}}}=\sqrt{{{x}-{2}}}-{1}</m></li> 
<li><m>\displaystyle{f{{\left({x}\right)}}}=\sqrt{{{x}+{2}}}+{1}</m></li> 
<li><m>\displaystyle{f{{\left({x}\right)}}}=\sqrt{{{x}+{2}}}-{1}</m></li> 
</ol></p>
<p>The graph of <m>\displaystyle{f{{\left({x}\right)}}}</m>  stretched vertically by a factor of 4.</p>
<p><ol style="list-style-type:upper-alpha"><li><m>\displaystyle{f{{\left({x}\right)}}}=\sqrt{{\frac{{1}}{{4}}{x}}}</m></li> 
<li><m>\displaystyle{f{{\left({x}\right)}}}=\frac{{1}}{{4}}\sqrt{{{x}}}</m></li> 
<li><m>\displaystyle{f{{\left({x}\right)}}}={4}\sqrt{{{x}}}</m></li> 
<li><m>\displaystyle{f{{\left({x}\right)}}}=\sqrt{{{4}{x}}}</m></li> 
</ol></p>


</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>A: <m>\displaystyle{f{{\left({x}\right)}}}=\sqrt{{-{x}}}</m></li><li>C: <m>\displaystyle{f{{\left({x}\right)}}}=\sqrt{{{x}-{2}}}</m></li><li>B: <m>\displaystyle{f{{\left({x}\right)}}}=\sqrt{{{x}}}-{3}</m></li><li>A: <m>\displaystyle{f{{\left({x}\right)}}}=\sqrt{{{x}-{2}}}+{1}</m></li><li>C: <m>\displaystyle{f{{\left({x}\right)}}}={4}\sqrt{{{x}}}</m></li></ul></p>
</solution>
</myopenmath>

